line_2: Which to delight her seem'd delighted.

line_1: By Beauty's self, by Love invited,
Or by an emulous Pride invited,
line_2: In which my Mother most delighted.

line_1: What need I be call'd? — Let the Dean be invited.
line_2: If with Humour and Wit you would have him delighted.

line_1: Have on my birth-day been invited
line_2: (But I was forc'd in verse to write it)

line_1: OF old, when Scarron his companions invited,
line_2: Each guest brought his dish, and the feast was united;
